Denver Crime Data - EDA

Lucas Stephens

3/12/2019

Import the data & load packages

library(tidyverse)
library(ggplot2)
library(lubridate)

df = read_csv(file='denver-crime-data/crime.csv.gz')

Add some features

df <- 
  df %>% mutate(
    day_of_week = wday(FIRST_OCCURRENCE_DATE, label = TRUE), 
    month = month(FIRST_OCCURRENCE_DATE, label = TRUE),
    date = date(FIRST_OCCURRENCE_DATE), 
    week = week(FIRST_OCCURRENCE_DATE),
    year = year(FIRST_OCCURRENCE_DATE), 
    hour = hour(FIRST_OCCURRENCE_DATE), 
    minute = minute(FIRST_OCCURRENCE_DATE), 
    type = case_when(
            IS_CRIME == 1 & IS_TRAFFIC == 0 ~ "Crime",
            IS_CRIME == 0 & IS_TRAFFIC == 1 ~ "Traffic",
            TRUE ~ "Both"
        )
  )

Set some colors

col_vector<-c('#e6194b', '#3cb44b', '#ffe119', '#4363d8', '#f58231', '#911eb4', '#46f0f0', '#f032e6', '#bcf60c', '#fabebe', '#008080', '#e6beff','#800000', '#aaffc3', '#ffd8b1', '#000075', '#808080', '#ffffff', '#000000')

dfm_color = "#387C70"
daily_count <- 
  df %>% count(date)

ggplot(daily_count, aes(x=date, y=n)) + 
  geom_line(color = dfm_color) + 
  theme_bw() + 
  ggtitle("Number of Incidents") + 
  ylab(element_blank()) + 
  xlab("Date") + 
  scale_x_date(date_breaks = "year") + 
  theme(panel.grid = element_blank(),
        plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5)) 

df <- 
  df %>% 
  filter(FIRST_OCCURRENCE_DATE >= date("2017-01-01"))

daily_count <- 
  df %>% count(date)

ggplot(daily_count, aes(x=date, y=n)) + 
  geom_line(color = dfm_color) + 
  theme_bw() + 
  ggtitle("Number of Incidents") + 
  ylab(element_blank()) + 
  xlab("Date") + 
  scale_x_date(date_breaks = "year") + 
  theme(panel.grid = element_blank(),
        plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5)) 

offense_daily_percentage <- 
  df %>% 
  mutate(
    month_year = date(paste0(year(date), "-", month(date, label =  FALSE), "-", "01"))
  ) %>% 
  count(month_year, OFFENSE_CATEGORY_ID) %>% 
  group_by(month_year) %>% 
  mutate(
    total = sum(n)
  ) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  mutate(
    percentage = n/total
  )

ggplot(offense_daily_percentage, aes(x=month_year, y=percentage)) +
  geom_area(aes(fill=OFFENSE_CATEGORY_ID)) +
  labs(title = "Incident Distribution Over Time",
       x = element_blank(),
       y = element_blank()) + 
  theme(panel.grid = element_blank(),
        plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5)) + 
  scale_fill_manual(values=col_vector)

monthly_offense_count <- 
  df %>% 
  count(month, year, OFFENSE_CATEGORY_ID)

ggplot(monthly_offense_count, aes(x=month, y=n)) +
  geom_point(aes(color=as.character(year))) + 
  theme_bw() + 
  labs(title = "Year over Year Incident Comparison",
       x = element_blank(),
       y = element_blank(),
       color = "Year") + 
  theme(panel.grid = element_blank(),
        plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5)) + 
  scale_color_manual(values=col_vector) + 
  facet_wrap(~ OFFENSE_CATEGORY_ID, scales = "free_y") +
  scale_x_discrete(breaks = c("Jan", "Mar", "May", "Jul", "Sep", "Nov"))
